ames adds complexity. I need to avoid direct reflection but still utilize URLClassLoader correctly for dynamic loading. It's a bit of a challenge!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing JLine dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the best approach to handle the jline dependencies. Directly using reflection doesn’t seem wise unless the public API explicitly requires it. Calling getConsole through reflection feels questionable to me. Maybe I could compile tests separately instead of mixing everything? Including only jline V2 might cover more functionalities, but that leaves V1 uncovered, which could be acceptable. The task asks for improvement, so I need to find a balance between coverage and simplicity. It's a bit of a juggling act!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XQYzfMFm0lpjwkQT4v8WEbcZ|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815a481969603bc5b5c80bd4e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaAdapterTest.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_b3yB8uJgbGveEWmXNyKiCWrI|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815b4819690e826fc1086d331", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/NativeJavaObjectTest.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FpZzqnYGwplMWm9WOtpPEcFO|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815c08196b96b0be18848ce9e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/reports/dynamic-access -type f -maxdepth 5 -print | head -20 && find tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access -type f -maxdepth 5 -print | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3874, "output": 782, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19504, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781042086238, "responseId": "resp_096c0371f96f3d38016a288ba695f4819696923b20c0383f0d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_XQYzfMFm0lpjwkQT4v8WEbcZ|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815a481969603bc5b5c80bd4e", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sourceforge_htmlunit.htmlunit_core_js;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.BaseFunction;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Context;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Function;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.JavaAdapter;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeJavaClass;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ObjToIntMap;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptRuntime;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptableObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Wrapper;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class JavaAdapterTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsAdapterBytecodeForClassAndInterfaceMethods() {\n        ObjToIntMap functionNames = new ObjToIntMap();\n        functionNames.put(\"run\", 0);\n        functionNames.put(\"customValue\", 1);\n\n        byte[] adapterCode =\n                JavaAdapter.createAdapterCode(\n                        functionNames,\n                        \"GeneratedAdapterBaseMarkerAdapter\",\n                        AdapterBase.class,\n                        new Class<?>[] {AdapterMarker.class},\n                        null);\n\n        assertThat(adapterCode).isNotEmpty();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsAdapterFromJavaScriptAndRoundTripsSerializationDescriptor() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            createAdapterFromJavaScriptAndRoundTripSerializationDescriptor();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void createAdapterFromJavaScriptAndRoundTripSerializationDescriptor()\n            throws Exception {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            JavaAdapter.init(context, scope, false);\n            RecordingFunction runFunction = new RecordingFunction();\n            RecordingFunction customValueFunction = new RecordingFunction();\n            ScriptRuntime.setFunctionProtoAndParent(runFunction, context, scope);\n            ScriptRuntime.setFunctionProtoAndParent(customValueFunction, context, scope);\n            NativeObject implementation = new NativeObject();\n            ScriptRuntime.setObjectProtoAndParent(implementation, scope);\n            implementation.defineProperty(\"run\", runFunction, ScriptableObject.EMPTY);\n            implementation.defineProperty(\n                    \"customValue\", customValueFunction, ScriptableObject.EMPTY);\n\n            Object constructor = ScriptableObject.getProperty(scope, \"JavaAdapter\");\n            Object wrapper =\n                    Function.class\n                            .cast(constructor)\n                            .construct(\n                                    context,\n                                    scope,\n                                    new Object[] {\n                                        new NativeJavaClass(scope, AdapterBase.class),\n                                        new NativeJavaClass(scope, AdapterMarker.class),\n                                        implementation\n                                    });\n\n            assertThat(wrapper).isInstanceOf(Wrapper.class);\n            Object adapter = ((Wrapper) wrapper).unwrap();\n            assertThat(adapter).isInstanceOf(AdapterMarker.class);\n            AdapterMarker marker = AdapterMarker.class.cast(adapter);\n            assertThat(marker.baseValue()).isEqualTo(\"base\");\n            marker.run();\n            assertThat(runFunction.callCount()).isOne();\n\n            detachFromScope(implementation);\n            detachFromScope(runFunction);\n            detachFromScope(customValueFunction);\n\n            Object copiedAdapter = roundTripAdapter(scope, adapter);\n            assertThat(copiedAdapter).isInstanceOf(AdapterMarker.class);\n            assertThat(AdapterMarker.class.cast(copiedAdapter).baseValue()).isEqualTo(\"base\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void detachFromScope(ScriptableObject scriptableObject) {\n        scriptableObject.setParentScope(null);\n        scriptableObject.setPrototype(null);\n    }\n\n    private Object roundTripAdapter(Scriptable scope, Object adapter) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            JavaAdapter.writeAdapterObject(adapter, output);\n        }\n\n        try (ObjectInputStream input =\n                new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes.toByteArray()))) {\n            return JavaAdapter.readAdapterObject(scope, input);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public interface AdapterMarker extends Runnable {\n        String baseValue();\n    }\n\n    public static class AdapterBase implements AdapterMarker, Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        @Override\n        public String baseValue() {\n            return \"base\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void run() {}\n\n        public Object customValue(Object value) {\n            return value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingFunction extends BaseFunction implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private int callCount;\n\n        @Override\n        public Object call(\n                Context context,\n                Scriptable scope,\n                Scriptable thisObj,\n                Object[] args) {\n            callCount++;\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        int callCount() {\n            return callCount;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781042104299}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_b3yB8uJgbGveEWmXNyKiCWrI|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815b4819690e826fc1086d331", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sourceforge_htmlunit.htmlunit_core_js;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.BaseFunction;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Context;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Function;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.JavaAdapter;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeArray;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeJavaClass;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeJavaObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptRuntime;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptableObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Wrapper;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.serialize.ScriptableInputStream;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.serialize.ScriptableOutputStream;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class NativeJavaObjectTest {\n    @Test\n    void convertsNativeArrayToJavaArray() {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            NativeArray array = new NativeArray(new Object[] {\"alpha\", \"beta\"});\n            ScriptRuntime.setObjectProtoAndParent(array, scope);\n\n            Object converted = Context.jsToJava(array, String[].class);\n\n            assertThat(converted).isInstanceOf(String[].class);\n            assertThat((String[]) converted).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void convertsJavaObjectWithDoubleValueMethodToPrimitiveDouble() {\n        Object converted = Context.jsToJava(new DoubleValueProvider(12.5), Double.TYPE);\n\n        assertThat(converted).isEqualTo(12.5);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void roundTripsWrappedSerializableJavaObject() throws Exception {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            NativeJavaObject original =\n                    new NativeJavaObject(\n                            scope,\n                            new SerializableBox(\"wrapped\", 42),\n                            SerializableBox.class);\n\n            NativeJavaObject copied = roundTrip(scope, original);\n\n            assertThat(copied.unwrap()).isInstanceOf(SerializableBox.class);\n            SerializableBox box = (SerializableBox) copied.unwrap();\n            assertThat(box.name()).isEqualTo(\"wrapped\");\n            assertThat(box.count()).isEqualTo(42);\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void roundTripsWrappedJavaAdapter() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            roundTripWrappedJavaAdapter();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void roundTripWrappedJavaAdapter() throws Exception {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            Object adapterWrapper = createAdapterWrapper(context, scope);\n\n            NativeJavaObject copied = roundTrip(scope, (NativeJavaObject) adapterWrapper);\n\n            assertThat(copied.unwrap()).isInstanceOf(AdapterMarker.class);\n            AdapterMarker marker = (AdapterMarker) copied.unwrap();\n            assertThat(marker.label()).isEqualTo(\"adapter-label\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private Object createAdapterWrapper(Context context, ScriptableObject scope) {\n        JavaAdapter.init(context, scope, false);\n        RecordingFunction labelFunction = new RecordingFunction(\"adapter-label\");\n        ScriptRuntime.setFunctionProtoAndParent(labelFunction, context, scope);\n        NativeObject implementation = new NativeObject();\n        ScriptRuntime.setObjectProtoAndParent(implementation, scope);\n        implementation.defineProperty(\"label\", labelFunction, ScriptableObject.EMPTY);\n\n        Object constructor = ScriptableObject.getProperty(scope, \"JavaAdapter\");\n        Object adapterWrapper =\n                Function.class\n                        .cast(constructor)\n                        .construct(\n                                context,\n                                scope,\n                                new Object[] {\n                                    new NativeJavaClass(scope, AdapterMarker.class),\n                                    implementation\n                                });\n\n        assertThat(adapterWrapper).isInstanceOf(Wrapper.class);\n        assertThat(((Wrapper) adapterWrapper).unwrap()).isInstanceOf(AdapterMarker.class);\n        return adapterWrapper;\n    }\n\n    private NativeJavaObject roundTrip(Scriptable scope, NativeJavaObject object) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ScriptableOutputStream output = new ScriptableOutputStream(bytes, scope)) {\n            output.writeObject(object);\n        }\n        try (ScriptableInputStream input =\n                new ScriptableInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes.toByteArray()), scope)) {\n            return (NativeJavaObject) input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public interface AdapterMarker {\n        String label();\n    }\n\n    public static final class DoubleValueProvider {\n        private final double value;\n\n        public DoubleValueProvider(double value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        public Number doubleValue() {\n            return value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class SerializableBox implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final String name;\n        private final int count;\n\n        public SerializableBox(String name, int count) {\n            this.name = name;\n            this.count = count;\n        }\n\n        public String name() {\n            return name;\n        }\n\n        public int count() {\n            return count;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingFunction extends BaseFunction implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final String result;\n\n        private RecordingFunction(String result) {\n            this.result = result;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Object call(\n                Context context,\n                Scriptable scope,\n                Scriptable thisObj,\n                Object[] args) {\n            return result;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781042104299}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FpZzqnYGwplMWm9WOtpPEcFO|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bb815c08196b96b0be18848ce9e", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\ntests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/htmlunit-core-js-2.70.0/reflection-calls.json\ntests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/htmlunit-core-js-2.70.0/resource-calls.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781042104304}]}
