Stream(ByteArrayOutputStream, true, UTF_8)` since that constructor is available starting from Java 10. I'll use `StandardCharsets.UTF_8`, and I realize I don’t need to add comments here. It's just about cleaning up the output process!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about working on the test class and methods. I wonder if package-private is the way to go, although it seems like using public methods might work too. I'll need to edit the build.gradle file and add the dependency, specifically \\\"testImplementation 'jline:jline:2.14.6'.\\\" It’s crucial to confirm that the version is stable. Oh, and should I consider htmlunit-core-js as optional? I’ll check the pom for that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nZ3WWpXzh9YDl6Y1ESHNODUS|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288be1dd088196bd9bf38f63a83cc5", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0 -maxdepth 4 -type f \\( -name 'pom.xml' -o -name '*.pom' \\) -print && rg \"jline\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0 -n | head -30"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 456, "output": 1237, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30365, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781042112396, "responseId": "resp_096c0371f96f3d38016a288bc0fea881968d060cd71cab57ab"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_nZ3WWpXzh9YDl6Y1ESHNODUS|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288be1dd088196bd9bf38f63a83cc5", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/net.source