y specific packages like `net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs` for reflection. \\n\\nShould I set up the `URLClassLoader` with a parent null to load Java from the bootstrap? I think it will load HTMLUnit and its dependencies from URLs, but I should verify if I need transitive dependencies. I must also check for potential conflicts with loading context via `Class.forName`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pjH65o8UBTz7GJqLg3PmJhFg|fc_096c0371f96f3d38016a288d01da4c8196856cef9cf256c857", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\ndependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'jline:jline:2.14.6'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n", "newText": "String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\nString jlineOneClasspathProperty = \"htmlunitCoreJs.jlineOneClasspath\"\n\nconfigurations {\n    jlineOneRuntime\n}\n\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    systemProperty jlineOneClasspathProperty, configurations.jlineOneRuntime.asPath\n}\n\ntasks.named(\"nativeTest\") {\n    runtimeArgs.add(\"-D${jlineOneClasspathProperty}=${configurations.jlineOneRuntime.asPath}\")\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'jline:jline:2.14.6'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n\n    jlineOneRuntime \"net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:$libraryVersion\"\n    jlineOneRuntime 'jline:jline:1.0'\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 412, "output": 1766, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39554, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781042394628, "responseI